f |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref> It was scored 33 points in the session 11 match between Prince Edward Island (Smith) and Newfoundland (Piercey). The score is 17\u201316 in the extra end. Previously, this result was in 1932 (session 6, Ontario (Bulley) - new Brunswick (Thibodeau), 17-16) and in 1957 (session 2, Saskatchewan (Campbell) - new Brunswick (Everett), 30 - 3).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n{{Canadian Men's Curling Championships}}\n\n[[Category:The Brier|1968]]\n[[Category:Curling in British Columbia]]\n[[Category:1968 in British Columbia]]\n[[Category:March 1968 sports events in Canada]]\n[[Category:1968 in curling]]\n[[Category:Sport in Kelowna]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox curling\n| Name = 1968 Macdonald Brier\n| Logo = \n| Size = \n| Host city = [[Kelowna, British Columbia]]<ref name=\"MontGaz4\">{{cite news |title=Ontario rated Brier dark horse |date=1968-03-04 |page=24 |newspaper=The Montreal Gazette |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1946&dat=19680304&id=G4IuAAAAIBAJ&sjid=AqAFAAAAIBAJ&pg=4116,565151&hl=en |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n| Arena = [[Kelowna Arena]]<ref name=\"soudog1968pdf\">{{cite news|title=BRIER BY THE NUMBERS |date=1969-02-10 |page=8 |url=http://soudogcurling.tripod.com/Brier/BrierRecords.pdf |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n| Dates =  March 4-8<ref>{{cite news|title=1968 MacDonald Brier - Scores |url=https://www.curlingzone.com/event.php?eventid=63&view=Scores&showdrawid=1#1 |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n| Attendance = 25,813<ref name=\"soudog1968\">{{cite news|title=1968 MacDonald Brier |url=http://soudogcurling.tripod.com/Brier/1968.htm |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n| Winner = '''{{AB}}'''\n| Curling club = [[Calgary Curling Club|Calgary CC]], [[Calgary]]\n| Skip = [[Ron Northcott]]\n| Third = [[Jim Shields]]\n| Second = [[Bernie Sparkes]]\n| Lead = [[Fred Storey]]\n| Finalist =  {{SK}}\n|Curling club2 = [[Avonlea Curling Club]] ([[Avonlea, Saskatchewan]])\n|Skip2 = [[Bob Pickering]]\n|Third2 = [[Jack Keys (curler)|Jack Keys]]\n|Second2 = [[Garnet Campbell]]\n|Lead2 = [[Gary Ford]]\n|Alternate2 = \n|Coach2 = \n|Finalist2 = \n| prev = [[1967 Macdonald Brier|1967]]\n| next = [[1969 Macdonald Brier|1969]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1968 [[Macdonald Brier]]''', Canada's national men's [[curling]] championship was held March 4&ndash;8 at the [[Kelowna Arena]] in [[Avonlea, Saskatchewan]].\n\nThe Ron Northcott rink representing Alberta won their second title with an impressive 9-1 record. It was also the 10th title for Alberta.\n\nSaskatchewan were runners-up, with 8-2 record. Prince Edward Island were at the third place at 7-3 records<ref name=\"MontGaz9\">{{cite news |title=Ron Northcott repeats '66 Brier win |date=1968-03-09 |page=8 |newspaper=The Montreal Gazette |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=Fr8DH2VBP9sC&dat=19680309&printsec=frontpage&hl=en |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>.\n\n==Teams==\n{| border=1 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0\n|-\n!style=\"background:#05f; width:200px;\"|Alberta\n!style=\"background:#09f; width:200px;\"|British Columbia\n!style=\"background:#ff9; width:200px;\"|Manitoba\n|-\n|[[Calgary Curling Club|Calgary CC]], [[Calgary]]\n'''Skip:''' [[Ron Northcott]]<br>\n'''Third:''' [[Jim Shields]]<br>\n'''Second:''' [[Bernie Sparkes]]<br>\n'''Lead''' [[Fred Storey]]\n|''[[Richmond Winter Club]], [[Richmond, British Columbia|Richmond]]''\n'''Skip:''' [[Bob McCubbin]]<br>\n'''Third:''' [[Jack Tucker (curler)|Jack Tucker]]<br>\n'''Second:''' [[Ed Trimble]]<br>\n'''Lead:''' [[Keith Issac]]\n|''[[Dauphin Curling Club|Dauphin CC]], [[Dauphin, Manitoba|Dauphin]]''\n'''Skip:''' [[Burke Parker]]<br>\n'''Third:''' [[Lloyd Yerama]]<br>\n'''Second:''' [[Roy Berry]]<br>\n'''Lead:''' [[Jack Yuill (curler)|Jack Yuill]]\n|-\n!style=\"background:#ff3; width:250px;\"|New Brunswick\n!style=\"background:#f57; width:250px;\"|Newfoundland\n!style=\"background:#0c6; width:250px;\"|Northern Ontario\n|-\n|''[[Fredericton Curlers Club|Fredericton CC]], [[Fredericton]]''