 Saskatchewan)|Avonlea CC]], [[Avonlea, Saskatchewan|Avonlea]]''\n'''Skip:''' [[Bob Pickering]]<br>\n'''Third:''' [[Jack Keys (curler)|Jack Keys]]<br>\n'''Second:''' [[Garnet Campbell (curler)|Garnet Campbell]]<br>\n'''Lead:''' [[Gary L. Ford|Gary Ford]]\n|}\n\n==Round robin standings==\nThe final standings were as follows:<ref name=\"MontGaz9\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!colspan=2|Key\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ffffcc; width:20px;\"|\n|align=left|Brier champion \n|}\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Province !! Skip !! W !! L\n|- bgcolor=#ffffcc\n| {{gold01}} || {{AB}} || [[Ron Northcott]] || 9 || 1\n|-\n| {{silver02}} || {{SK}} || [[Bob Pickering]] || 8 || 2\n|- \n| {{bronze03}} || {{PE}} || [[Alan F. Smith|Alan Smith]] || 7 || 3 \n|-\n| 4 || {{NB}} || [[Jim Ayer]] || 6 || 4\n|- \n| 4 || {{ON}} || [[Don Gilbert]] || 6 || 4\n|-\n| 6 || {{BC}} || [[Bob McCubbin]] || 5 || 5\n|-\n| 7 || {{MB}} || [[Burke Parker]] || 4 || 6\n|-\n| 7 || {{NS}} || [[Don Flemming]] || 4 || 6\n|-\n| 9 || {{QC}} || [[Bill Tracy]] || 3 || 7\n|-\n| 10 || {{NL}} || [[Bill Piercey]] || 2 || 8\n|-\n| 11 || {{NO}} || [[Herbert Pile]] || 1 || 9 \n|}\n\n==Round robin results==\n===Draw 1===\n''Monday, March 4, 4:00pm''<ref name=\"MontGaz5\">{{cite news |title=Quebec's Tracy falls 11-5 to Pickering |date=1968-03-05 |page=27 |newspaper=The Montreal Gazette |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=Fr8DH2VBP9sC&dat=19680305&printsec=frontpage&hl=en |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n{{Curlingbox12\n| sheet = \n| team1 = {{QC}} (Tracy)\n|0|0|2|0|1|0|0|1|1|0|0|0| |5\n| team2 = {{SK}} (Pickering)\n|2|1|0|2|0|2|0|0|0|1|1|2| |11\n}}\n{{Curlingbox12\n| sheet = \n| team1 = {{NL}} (Piercey)\n|0|0|0|1|0|0|0|2|0|1|0|1| |5\n| team2 = {{AB}} (\u041d\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0442\u0442)\n|0|0|2|0|1|2|2|0|3|0|3|0| |13\n}}\n{{Curlingbox12\n| sheet = \n| team1 = {{NO}} (Pile)\n|0|4|0|0|2|0|2|0|1|0|0|1| |10\n| team2 = {{BC}} (McCubbin)\n|2|0|2|1|0|1|0|4|0|0|1|0| |11\n}}\n{{Curlingbox12