in\n| note15          = featuring [[2Pac]]\n| writer15        = {{hlist|Atkins|Lorenzo|[[Dave Grusin]]|[[Earl Klugh]]|[[Tupac Shakur]]|[[Stretch (rapper)|Randy Walker]]}}\n| extra15         = {{hlist|Irv Gotti|Lil' Rob}}\n| length15        = 5:03\n| title16         = Pain Is Love\n| note16          = \n| writer16        = {{hlist|Atkins|Aurelius|Lorenzo}}\n| extra16         = Irv Gotti\n| length16        = 5:04\n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n*{{sup|{{note|a|[a]}}}} signifies a co-producer\n\n'''Sample credits'''\n* \"Dial M for Murder\" contains interpolations of \"Castle Walls\", written by [[Dennis DeYoung]] and performed by [[Styx (band)|Styx]].\n* \"Livin' It Up\" contains excerpts from \"[[Do I Do]]\", written and performed by [[Stevie Wonder]].\n*\"I'm Real (Murder Remix)\" contains an interpolation of \"[[All Night Long (Mary Jane Girls song)|All Night Long]]\" written by [[Rick James]] and performed by [[Mary Jane Girls]].\n*\"So Much Pain\" contains excerpts from \"Pain\", written by [[Dave Grusin]], [[Earl Klugh]], [[Tupac Shakur]], and [[Stretch (rapper)|Randy Walker]], and performed by [[2Pac]] featuring [[Stretch (rapper)|Stretch]].\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2001-02)\n!align=\"left\"|Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|6|artist=Ja Rule|album=Pain Is Love}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|[[Canadian Albums Chart]]\n|align=\"center\"|3 \n|-\n{{album chart|Germany|38|artist=Ja Rule|album=Pain Is Love}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland|24|year=2002|week=9}}\n|-\n{{album chart|New Zealand|1|artist=Ja Rule|album=Pain Is Love}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|28|artist=Ja Rule|album=Pain Is Love}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK|3|artist=Ja Rule}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|1|artist=Ja Rule|artistid=276599|accessdate=May 6, 2015}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRandBHipHop|1|artist=Ja Rule|artistid=276599|accessdate=May 6, 2015}}\n|-\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable 